Hooks?
Hooks in Liferay are used to customize or extend the portalâ€™s core functionality without modifying the core source code
it were used in older liferay version 
in liferay 7+ hooks are replaced by osgi modules.

Pre-hook
A pre-hook is always invoked before the user login,
and in OSGi we define it by using @Component(property = {"key=login.events.pre"}) inside the Java class

Pre-hook
A post-hook is always invoked after the user login,
and in OSGi we define it by using @Component(property = {"key=login.events.post"}) inside the Java clcass
class implement's LifecycleAction 


